
[1]industry

   IN'DUSTRY, n. [L. industria.] Habitual diligence in any employment,
   either bodily or mental; steady attention to business; assiduity;
   opposed to sloth and idleness. We are directed to take lessons of
   industry from the bee. Industry pays debts, while idleness or despair
   will increase them.
